OL,3,CWHO declares global health emergency
OL,4,Cover Ebola outbreak in Congo and Uganda
OL,6,FEbola is highly contagious and can be
OL,7,Fcontracted via bodily fluids such as
OL,8,Fvomit, blood or semen. The disease it
OL,9,Fcauses is rare, but severe and often
OL,10,Ffatal.
OL,12,FHealth authorities have confirmed the
OL,13,Fcurrent outbreak is caused by the
OL,14,FBundibugyo virus, a rare variant of
OL,15,Fthe Ebola disease that has no approved
OL,16,Ftherapeutics or vaccines.
OL,18,FAlthough more than 20 Ebola outbreaks
OL,19,Fhave taken place in Congo and Uganda,
OL,20,Fthis is only the third time the
OL,21,FBundibugyo virus has been reported.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
