PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1779045069
OL,3,CWHO declares global health emergency
OL,4,Cover Ebola outbreak in Congo and Uganda
OL,6,FThe two cases had no apparent links to
OL,7,Feach other, and both patients had
OL,8,Ftravelled from Congo, it added.
OL,10,FThe Bundibugyo virus was first
OL,11,Fdetected in Uganda's Bundibugyo
OL,12,Fdistrict during a 2007-2008 outbreak
OL,13,Fthat infected 149 people and killed 37
OL,14,Fpeople. The second time was in 2012 in
OL,15,Fan outbreak in Isiro, Congo, where 57
OL,16,Fcases and 29 deaths were reported.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
